                    <head>Tractatus de passione Domini; miscellaneous theological texts</head>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <note>Flyleaves removed. A small fragment still visible in upper left corner of <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>.</note>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure type="leftFlyleaves" unit="folios"/>
                                    <measure type="rightFlyleaves" unit="folios"/>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>Modern foliation in pencil. The foliation on the majority of the leaves has been corrected, which sometimes has lead to further errors in the foliation: 1-228, 228bis, 229-240, 242, 242bis, 243-277.</foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <formula>1-16(12), 17(12+2), 18(10), 19(12), 20(14), 21-23(12)</formula>
                                    <p>
                                        <ref target="https://vceditor.library.upenn.edu/project/697350cd7552230001633ff3/viewOnly">VisColl collation</ref>. Parchment guards with visible text.</p>
                                    <signatures>
                                        <locus from="207" to="266" scheme="folios"/>: quire singatures in Arabic numerals in red ink at the beginning of quires. </signatures>
                                    <catchwords>
                                        <locus from="12v" to="204v" scheme="folios"/>: Catchwords by one or several contemporary hands. </catchwords>
                                </collation>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top left corner: National Library book label with current signum; top of page, in ink by a medieval hand: <quote>ccc x v i?</quote>. The inner cover is also covered with offprint, probably from a detached flyleaf.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>There is some visible offprint on the inner cover, probably from a detached flyleaf.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true">
                                <p>Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 3 double raised band and endbands. Originally, 2 clasps on leather straps. Originally, centre and corner buckles on each cover. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>, fragment of a label with illegbile text by a medieval hand. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, ink on paper label: <quote>Tractatus de Pass<supplied reason="omitted">ione</supplied> Domini cum aliis B 16</quote>; stamped in gold: <quote>A 197</quote>.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="230" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="170" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="75" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="tooling">
                                    <p>Both covers are decorated with geometrical patterns that seem to have been made in ink.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <condition>Leather worn and heavily damaged by bookworms. Buckles, clasps, and catch plates missing. Board attachments visible on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100104">Germany</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1401">15th century</origDate>. The last two texts mention the dates <date when="1450"/> and <date when="1451"/> (<locus from="271vb" to="271vb" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="275ra" to="275ra" scheme="folios"/>), the latter also concerns <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100278">Salzburg</placeName>, which may point to an Austrian origin for the entire or part of the manuscripts. The watermark for the first part of the manuscript also indicates Bavaria or Austria. </p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown. The signum <quote>B 16</quote> on the <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/> has not been identified.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Purchased from the bookdealer <persName>F. Butsch</persName> in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100004">Augsburg</placeName> by the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> in <date when="1873"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
                    <msPart>
                        <msIdentifier>
